commText: Rahane and Gaikwad are at the crease. Rahane is on strike. Matt Henry will open the attack

Matt Henry to Rahane, 1 run, fuller delivery shaping back in towards off stump. Rahane plays a forward defence onto the pitch and hares off for a single. Henry tries to kick it onto the stumps but his footwork isn't as good as his swing bowling
Matt Henry to Gaikwad, no run, 136.8 clicks, a big inswinger from a length. Goes over the off stump as Ruturaj leaves it alone.
Matt Henry to Gaikwad, 2 runs, this time an away swinger from a length. Ends outside off and Ruturaj dabs it late towards wide third-man for a couple of runs
Matt Henry to Gaikwad, 1 run, a bit fuller and angling in towards off stump, run down towards third-man
Matt Henry getting some swing early on. The batters are playing the ball late
Matt Henry to Rahane, no run, 135.7 clicks, stump lined delivery from a length. Solidly defended
Matt Henry to Rahane, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Matt Henry to Rahane, out Caught by Rahul!! Edged & gone! KL Rahul leaps to his right, full stretch like Manuel Neuer and plucks out a stunner!! Matt Henry with that nagging Test match length, in the corridor of uncertainity and Rahane tries to drive at it. Takes an edge and Rahul leaps rightward to claim a one-handed catch. CSK and Rahane's travails with the powerplay continue. Rahane c Rahul b Matt Henry 1(3)
CSK opening partnership this IPL Inns: 8 Runs: 171 Avg: 21.37 RR: 8.27 50+: 1 - CSK's opening stand aggregate runs and average are the lowest among all teams.
Ajinkya Rahane vs Pacers this IPL Inns: 7 Runs: 120 Balls: 84 Dismissals: 5 Avg: 24.0 SR: 142.85
Daryl Mitchell, right handed bat, comes to the crease
Mohsin Khan, left-arm fast medium, comes into the attack
Mohsin Khan to Gaikwad, 1 run, fuller delivery angling across. Ruturaj opens the bat face towards third-man

Mohsin Khan to Mitchell, FOUR, fumble and that's the first boundary!! Angling across outside off at a gentle punch. Punched square of the wicket and goes through the hands of Badoni at point. Mitchell off the mark with four

Mohsin Khan to Mitchell, 1 run, dropped!! Mohsin Khan angling one across and gets a bit of extra bounce. Daryl Mitchell with a slash and the ball flies off the outside edge towards short third. Yash Thakur the fielder who lobs it over his head trying to catch it. A regulation chance goes begging...
Mohsin Khan to Gaikwad, FOUR, top shot from the skipper!! Back of length and slightly wide, Ruturaj punches it on the up and square of the wicket for a boundary

Mohsin Khan to Gaikwad, FOUR, a cover drive that can be framed at the Chepauk dressing room!! Fuller and angling across, Gaikwad with a big stride forwards to reach the ball and drives it through extra cover for a boundary. The CSK skipper is looking at home
Mohsin Khan to Gaikwad, 2 runs, on a length and angling wide outside off, dabbed towards third-man and hit fine enough to pick up a couple of runs. End of an eventful over from Mohsin Khan
Matt Henry to Mitchell, no run, 137.3 clicks, a fraction fuller and just outside off. Mitchell goes for a big swipe at it and inside halves it along the ground towards mid-wicket

Matt Henry to Mitchell, 2 runs, an uppish drive to this wide, fuller delivery from Henry. Goes past short cover and the outfield is a bit sluggish as the ball goes begrudgingly towards the boundary. Pooran from mid-off runs back, puts it a dive and saves a couple of runs for his side
Matt Henry to Mitchell, no run, fuller delivery outside off, tails inwards slightly and the bat turns on impact with the delivery. Inside halved towards mid-wicket
Matt Henry to Mitchell, 1 run, good length and shaping inwards, nice and tight at the stumps. Mitchell pushes it to the left of short cover for a single
Matt Henry to Gaikwad, 2 runs, a fraction shorter and on the thigh pad, tucked softly behind square for a couple of runs
Matt Henry to Gaikwad, no run, fuller and shaping away slightly from off. Was a bit slower than the earlier deliveries. Ruturaj defends it late towards short cover
Ravi Bishnoi, right-arm leg break, comes into the attack
Ravi Bishnoi to Mitchell, 1 run, fuller at the stumps, Mitchell shuffles inwards and sweeps in front of square to deep mid-wicket
Ravi Bishnoi to Gaikwad, FOUR, very full outside off, Gaikwad plays it late and opens the bat face intricately to get it square of the wicket for a boundary. Neat use of the wrists from Ruturaj

Ravi Bishnoi to Gaikwad, FOUR, a length ball outside off, was pushed from a flat trajectory. Gaikwad cuts at it and hits it a bit uppishly behind square. Henry from short third gets a hand to it after moving to his right but can only parry it towards the boundary. A very tough chance
Ravi Bishnoi to Gaikwad, 1 run, tossed up and closer to off, driven towards long-off
Ravi Bishnoi to Mitchell, 1 run, loopy delivery outside off, driven to long-off
Rahul gestures to Bishnoi asking him to bowl at the stumps, and not keep it wide
Ravi Bishnoi to Gaikwad, 1 run, full, flighted and wide. Driven through covers but the fielder makes a diving stop. Saves three runs for his side

Matt Henry to Gaikwad, FOUR, that shot belongs in a museum of modern art!! Henry errs by going too full outside off, with the vaining powers of swing as well. Gaikwad plants his front foot nicely forward and drives it through covers for a superb boundary
Matt Henry to Gaikwad, no run, Henry shortens the length slightly and takes some pace off. Ruturaj early on the drive and hits it tamely towards mid-off
Matt Henry to Gaikwad, FOUR, on a length and wide, Gaikwad waits till the last moment and then cuts it behind square to pick up a bounday. Waited till the very end to cut it away with finesse
Matt Henry to Gaikwad, 1 run, good length and angling inwards to the stumps. Squeezed towards backward point for a single
Matt Henry to Mitchell, 1 run, 137.8 clicks, fuller delivery onto middle stump. Pushed down to long-on
Matt Henry to Gaikwad, 1 run, fuller delivery that skids onto off stump. Pushed towards the point region for a single
Yash Thakur, right-arm medium, comes into the attack
Yash Thakur to Gaikwad, 1 run, full and angling onto the pads, clipped towards deep square
Yash Thakur to Mitchell, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Yash Thakur to Mitchell, out Caught by Hooda!! Gone!! I0$ A back of length delivery that was a bit slower. Mitchell waited and tried to pull it in front of square. Deepak Hooda dives to his left from mid-wicket and snaps up a ball that was travelling. Daryl Mitchell looked promising but is out cheaply. Mitchell c Hooda b Yash Thakur 11(10) [4s-1]
Ravindra Jadeja, left handed bat, comes to the crease
Yash Thakur to Jadeja, no run, good length delivery that angles onto off stump. Punched towards the cover fielder.
Another promotion for Jaddu. Comes to bat at number four once again against LSG

Yash Thakur to Jadeja, no run, 136 clicks, nips back from round the wicket and angles into the batter. Jadeja a bit uncomfortable and the ball sneaks between bat and body. A half shout for caught behind, no review taken
Yash Thakur to Jadeja, no run, back of length and angling inwards, Jadeja tries to pull it away but can't connect
Yash Thakur to Jadeja, no run, hard length and at the stumps, Jadeja dances down and hits it into the pitch back to Thakur. Just one run off the over, superb end to the powerplay for LSG

Summary (Overs 1-6) > Henry removes Rahane early > Mitchell dropped on 4 off Mohsin > Tough chance handed by Ruturaj dropped > Free-flowing Ruturaj picks off a flurry of boundaries > Yash Thakur gets rid of Mitchell
Ravi Bishnoi [1.0-0-12-0] is back into the attack
Ravi Bishnoi to Gaikwad, 1 run, googly that ends on off stump, dabbed towards gully for a single. A shout of 'yes' from Rahul. He's happier with this line
STAT: 37* off 19 is Gaikwad’s second highest score in the powerplay in the IPL, only behind 46* off 20 against the same team at the same venue last year.
Ravi Bishnoi to Jadeja, 1 run, slips out the hand and is a loopy full toss. Slammed down the ground but without any real venom behind it. Long-on cuts it off and just a single
Ravi Bishnoi to Gaikwad, no run, flighted up onto off, defended towards short cover
Ravi Bishnoi to Gaikwad, 1 run, tossed up on middle and leg, Ruturaj gets leg side and caresses it towards long-off

Ravi Bishnoi to Jadeja, FOUR, pushed fuller and quicker wide outside off. Jadeja picks it up from there and slams it down the ground. Hit straight enough and powerfully enough to give no chance to long-on
Ravi Bishnoi to Jadeja, no run, googly that gets a bit of extra bounce and ends outside off, over Jadeja's bat as he tried to cut it away
Marcus Stoinis, right-arm medium, comes into the attack
Stoinis to Gaikwad, 2 runs, full onto middle stump, Ruturaj neatly closes the bat face to get it towards deep square for a couple of runs
Stoinis to Gaikwad, 1 run, good length and wide, cut into the ground and square of the wicket, to the right of backward point
Stoinis to Jadeja, no run, back of length and angling onto the body. Jadeja tried to pull it away behind square but finds short fine
Stoinis to Jadeja, FOUR, short ball angling onto the body, this time pulled to the right of that short fine fielder for a boundary
Review taken by LSG for LBW. Stoinis super confident, he was pleading with the umpire in his appeal. Height perhaps the deterrent. Yes, would have gone over leg stump

Stoinis to Jadeja, leg byes, 1 run, review lost for LSG. On a length and angling inwards towards the front pad. Beats Jadeja on the inside edge and strikes the thigh pad, deflects towards point. Too high for an LBW
Stoinis to Gaikwad, 2 runs, good length at the stumps, Ruturaj shuffles away slightly to punch it in front of square for a couple of runs
Krunal Pandya, Left arm orthodox, comes into the attack
Krunal Pandya to Jadeja, no run, flat delivery on a length, spins back in. Jadeja dances out but is forced to defend
Krunal Pandya to Jadeja, 1 run, flat delivery and with the arm towards off, slapped down to long-on
Krunal Pandya to Gaikwad, 1 run, 104.3 clicks, darted through at the stumps. Pushed down to long-on from the crease
Krunal Pandya to Jadeja, 1 run, length ball on the pads, tucked towards short fine for a single
Krunal Pandya to Gaikwad, FOUR, pure timing on that one!! A length ball at over 100 clicks, Gaikwad hangs back and pulls it towards the geometric centre between deep mid-wicket and long-on
Krunal Pandya to Gaikwad, 1 run, quicker and pushed through on off, Gaikwad pushes it towards extra cover for a single. Fifty for the CSK skipper.

Time-out. Nicely poised game after nine overs. Ruturaj has done the bulk of the scoring on this track that is looking decent to bat on so far. LSG found early success with the swing of Matt Henry, but since then have failed to create too many chances. They have been a bit sloopy in the field as well. Let's see how the game continues...
Yash Thakur [1.0-0-1-1] is back into the attack
Yash Thakur to Gaikwad, 1 run, hard length delivery just outside off, run down to third-man

Most 50-plus scores as an opener for CSK (IPL) 17 - Ruturaj Gaikwad 16 - Faf du Plessis 13 - Michael Hussey 9 - Devon Conway 9 - Shane Watson 9 - Murali Vijay Gaikwad also becomes the 21st player to aggregate 2,000-plus runs as an opener in the IPL, first for CSK.
Thakur round the wicket
Yash Thakur to Jadeja, 1 run, length ball onto off stump, pulled towards deep mid-wicket

Yash Thakur to Gaikwad, FOUR, delicate from Ruturaj!! A short ball, was the slower bouncer. Gaikwad waits till the last moment and then calmly plays an upper cut over the keeper for a very fine boundary
Yash Thakur to Gaikwad, 2 runs, good length onto off stump, punched in front of square and gives Badoni quite a chase from sweeper cover. Two more runs taken
Yash Thakur to Gaikwad, 1 run, fuller delivery onto off, keeps a tad low. Squeezed towards backward point for a quick single
Yash Thakur to Jadeja, 2 runs, off cutter from a length, pulled to the left of deep mid-wicket for a couple of runs
Krunal Pandya to Gaikwad, no run, dances to the pitch on the drive but hits it towards extra cover
Krunal Pandya to Gaikwad, 1 run, 99.7 clicks, one of the slower deliveries by Krunal so far. Fuller delivery onto off, pushed to the left of covers for a single
Krunal Pandya to Jadeja, 1 run, flat and with the arm outside off, slapped down to long-off
Krunal Pandya to Gaikwad, FOUR, another arm ball, errs down leg almost. Ruturaj gets down on one knee and sweeps it to the left of short fine for a boundary
Krunal Pandya to Gaikwad, 1 run, pushed fuller outside off, Gaikwad leans closer and drives to sweeper cover
Krunal Pandya to Jadeja, leg byes, 1 run, darted onto the pads from a length, tickled towards short fine
Mohsin Khan [1.0-0-16-0] is back into the attack
Mohsin Khan to Jadeja, 1 run, Jadeja shuffles away and Mohsin follow him with this length ball. Tucked towards deep backward square leg

Mohsin Khan to Gaikwad, FOUR, Ruturaj is toying with the fielders here!! Superb finesse on that one. Was a cutter that ends just outside off, Gaikwad opens the bat face perfectly to the right of backward point and the ball trickles away for four
Mohsin Khan to Gaikwad, 2 runs, hard length and angling inwards to off from round the wicket. Cut behind square for a couple of runs. 50 partnership up
Mohsin Khan to Gaikwad, 1 run, full, wide and pace off. Ruturaj leans in for a square drive. There is a fielder in the deep so just a single
Mohsin Khan to Jadeja, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Mohsin Khan to Jadeja, out Caught by Rahul!! Soft dismissal! A slower delivery, back of length and angling into the batter. Jadeja has to wait an eternity to try and pull that away, but can only glove it through to the keeper. Lobs off the gloves and into the welcoming hands of KL Rahul. Nobody really appealed or even celebrated, as Jadeja quietly walked off the field. Jadeja c Rahul b Mohsin Khan 16(19) [4s-2]
Shivam Dube, left handed bat, comes to the crease
Mohsin Khan to Shivam Dube, 1 run, pitched up delivery, pushed a bit quicker. Driven towards mid-off for a single
Marcus Stoinis [1.0-0-9-0] is back into the attack
Stoinis to Shivam Dube, no run, pace off and angling onto the pads. Defended to mid-wicket
Stoinis to Shivam Dube, 1 run, length ball outside off, Dube punches it square of the wicket for a single
Stoinis to Gaikwad, no run, a slightly fuller length delivery onto off stump. Punched square of the wicket but towards the fielder
Stoinis to Gaikwad, 1 run, length ball on the thigh pad, pulled to deep backward square leg

Stoinis to Shivam Dube, SIX, in the arc, out the park!! Stoinis goes a bit too full at at the stumps, Dube with a lovely bat swing as he hoists it straight down the ground. Plenty of elevation but goes the distance as well for a maximum!! First six of the game.
Stoinis to Shivam Dube, 1 run, short of length and wide, Dube reaches out for it with no footwork and punches it behind square for a single
Matt Henry [3.0-0-20-1] is back into the attack
Matt Henry to Shivam Dube, FOUR, short pitched and at the body, Dube with a swivel pull that he tickles very fine to the right of the keeper.
Matt Henry to Shivam Dube, no run, hard length and angling across. Punched into the ground towards backward point
Matt Henry to Shivam Dube, 1 run, slower delivery onto middle stump. Pushed towards cover point for a single
Matt Henry to Gaikwad, no run, length ball just outside off, was pace off. Pulled into the ground but towards mid-wicket
Matt Henry to Gaikwad, 2 runs, short of length on off, pulled towards a vacant deep square region but cut off but the fielder at deep mid-wicket
Matt Henry to Gaikwad, 1 run, low full toss, angling at the stumps. Clipped towards deep mid-wicket
Stoinis to Gaikwad, SIX, first six for Gaikwad. A good length delivery on the stumps, he gets forward and pulls from there, deep mid-wicket was just a spectator
Stoinis to Gaikwad, 1 run, full on off, Gaikwad gets forward to drive, thick inside half down to long-on
Stoinis to Shivam Dube, FOUR, full on off, Shivam Dube with that batswing of his, hammers it straight down the ground, brute power and mid-off was inside
Stoinis to Shivam Dube, 1 run, slower ball off-cutter outside off, cut to sweeper cover
Stoinis to Gaikwad, wide, fullish and down leg, Gaikwad flicks and misses, wide
Stoinis to Gaikwad, 2 runs, good length on the stumps, Gaikwad pulls wide of deep square leg for a couple
Stoinis to Gaikwad, 1 run, good length on the stumps, Gaikwad makes room to dab it through point
Timeout! CSK set for 180 here. Gaikwad is playing such a brilliant knock. He would be eyeing to bat till the end.
Summary (Overs 7-15) > LSG spinners fail to make inroads > Ruturaj brings up 50 > Ruturaj and Jadeja share 50-run stand > Struggling Jadeja dismissed by Mohsin > Dube and Ruturaj up the ante
Yash Thakur [2.0-0-12-1] is back into the attack
Yash Thakur to Gaikwad, 1 run, good length outside off, Gaikwad dabs it with an open face to deep backward point
Yash Thakur to Shivam Dube, SIX, full on the pads, Shivam Dube flicks and it has enough to clear deep mid-wicket running to his right. And he did not get enough of it too
Yash Thakur to Shivam Dube, SIX, no such problems this time. Picks the slower ball off-cutter outside off, massacres the pull way back into the crowd at deep mid-wicket

Yash Thakur to Shivam Dube, SIX, hat-trick of sixes. Full on off, in the slot, Shivam Dube skies the loft and only for his power, did the ball clear long-on, any other man and it would have been a dolly to the fielder, the crowd though love it, they are losing their minds
Yash Thakur to Shivam Dube, no run, a stare from Yash Thakur at Shivam Dube after the batter inside-edges the pull, was the slower ball off-cutter again and Shivam Dube finds Rahul
Yash Thakur to Shivam Dube, no run, very full outside off, driven straight to the fielder at extra-cover
Mohsin Khan [2.0-0-25-1] is back into the attack
Mohsin Khan to Gaikwad, SIX, Gaikwad into the nineties. Another slower ball off-cutter outside off, too short and Gaikwad pulls to the deep mid-wicket stands
Mohsin Khan over the wicket.
Mohsin Khan to Gaikwad, no run, full and angling away from Gaikwad outside off, he shuffles across to sweep and misses

Mohsin Khan to Gaikwad, no run, slower ball off-cutter outside off, just inside the tramline, Gaikwad cuts and misses. He takes the review now for that. Gaikwad's back foot has moved outside the off-stump, so it's not a wide. CSK lose a review
Mohsin Khan to Gaikwad, 1 run, slower ball off-cutter outside off, cut to deep backward point
Mohsin Khan to Shivam Dube, 1 run, slower ball off-cutter outside off, cut to deep cover
Mohsin Khan to Gaikwad, no run, full and wide outside off, Gaikwad shuffles across to sweep and again misses
Rahul reviews for a wide call. He is having an animated chat with umpire Nikhil Patwardhan. And also has a word or two with Shivam Dube. The wide stays.
Yash Thakur to Shivam Dube, wide, Shivam Dube just moved a bit and the ball was on the tramline, the third ump feels nothing conclusive to overturn the original call, so the wide stays
Yash Thakur to Shivam Dube, no run, yorker length outside off, Shivam Dube fails to dig it away, good ball
Yash Thakur to Shivam Dube, 1 run, low full-toss outside off, Shivam Dube swings and the thick outside-edge rolls to short third man who is very fine, just one
Yash Thakur to Gaikwad, SIX, half-volley in the slot and Gaikwad has smashed the loft flat over long-on, Pooran is not happy with that delivery, mentions something to Yash Thakur
Yash Thakur round the wicket.

Yash Thakur to Gaikwad, FOUR, fine 100 from Gaikwad. He has his arms stretched and raises it. From ball one he was on tonight. Full outside off, he gets forward and lofts over extra-cover, another clean hit

Yash Thakur to Gaikwad, FOUR, Bishnoi runs to his left from deep mid-wicket and dives with outstretched hands but does not even get a fingertip on it, misjudged it. A slower ball off-cutter outside off, Gaikwad miscues the pull and gets away
Yash Thakur to Gaikwad, no run, full and wide outside off, Gaikwad mistimes the drive back to Yash Thakur
Mohsin Khan to Shivam Dube, SIX, Shivam Dube is on fire. Picks the slower ball off-cutter on a good length outside off, pulls massively over deep mid-wicket
Mohsin Khan to Shivam Dube, no run, full seam-up outside off, Shivam Dube finds extra-cover who is very straight
Mohsin Khan to Shivam Dube, FOUR, full and seam-up outside off, but Shivam Dube has crashed this one bounce over the ropes wide of extra-cover and the deep extra-cover. What power

Mohsin Khan to Shivam Dube, SIX, even MSD is clapping. Another slower ball which is full outside off, Shivam Dube lofts with force and it's a flat hit straight down the ground, did not get all of it too - 50 for Shivam Dube
IPL hundreds for CSK 2 - Murali Vijay 2 - Shane Watson 2 - Ruturaj Gaikwad 1 - Michael Hussey 1 - Brendon McCullum 1 - Suresh Raina 1 - Ambati Rayudu
Mohsin Khan to Shivam Dube, 1 run, dropped by de Kock. Full outside off, crashed hard and de Kock on the leap and reverse-cup fails to hang on. Shivam Dube is disappointed for not putting that away
Mohsin Khan to Gaikwad, no run, fullish outside off, Gaikwad swings and misses
Marcus Stoinis [3.0-0-34-0] is back into the attack
Stoinis to Shivam Dube, SIX, LSG are not learning. Again a slower ball off-cutter on a good length outside off, Shivam Dube is waiting and pulls over deep mid-wicket
Stoinis round the wicket.

Stoinis to Shivam Dube, 2 runs, direct-hit and Gaikwad was gone. A short ball off-pace dug in outside off, Shivam Dube miscues the pull and it's near mid-on, the fielder shies and misses, Gaikwad had given up
Stoinis to Shivam Dube, 2 runs, slower and shorter outside off, carved wide of deep backward point for another couple
Run-out check sent upstairs. Gone!
Stoinis to Shivam Dube, THATS OUT!! Run Out!!

Stoinis to Shivam Dube, out Shivam Dube Run Out!! Full outside off, driven to extra-cover and de Kock sends the throw on the bounce to Stoinis who does the rest. Shivam Dube did not dive and was slow. Caught short. Shivam Dube run out (de Kock/Stoinis) 66(27) [4s-3 6s-7]
And here comes MSD. Look at that cheer. And he won't be on strike either. I0$ The crowd though don't care and they are losing their pants in excitement. Humongous cheer when they saw MS walk out.
MS Dhoni, right handed bat, comes to the crease
Stoinis to Gaikwad, 1 run, a low full-toss outside off, Gaikwad shuffles across and sweeps to deep mid-wicket. Dhoni wants the strike and jogs to the other end

Can MS hit one out of the ground? Only one ball tonight to make an impact. Try telling that to this crowd. They have their mobile torches on and are absolutely loving every nano second of this. MS surveys the field.

Stoinis to Dhoni, FOUR, full outside off, not yorker length and Dhoni shuffles across to heave it to deep mid-wicket, right into the gap and the crowd get what they want. MS runs off and CSK end on 210

21:19 Local Time, 15:49 GMT, 21:19 IST: Superb effort from CSK to make 210 here. Rahane fell early and Mitchell at 3 failed to make an impact once more. But it was the Gaikwad show tonight. He was on from ball one and did not put a foot wrong. The timing, the placement and the class was all on display and he made it count with his 2nd IPL hundred. Jadeja was promoted to 4 again and he did not make many but it was the Dube-Gaikwad show after that. The left-hander was all power as he marmalised the LSG attack. The slower ball off-cutters on a good length into the pitch did not work at all as it sailed over deep mid-wicket far too many times. Dube's innings was the difference in the end as CSK went past 200. And the crowd got to see MS walk out and smash his only ball to the boundary. And boy did they love that or what. A huge chase for LSG coming up. Back for the reply in 5 minutes...

Shivam Dube: Especially the support from the crowd is amazing. We love to play in Chennai. All grounds are like home grounds but this is what pushes me a little more. Rutu needed 1 over to recover after playing for a long time so I decided to take the bowler on. We have scored a lot of runs, we are 10-15 runs above par. We definitely need to bowl well but we have got 10 runs more. Enjoyed a lot when Rutu bats, his class is on a different level.
Shivam Dube for CSK Inns: 33 Runs: 1018 Avg: 37.7 SR: 161.07 50s: 8 HS: 95*

STAT: Of the 13 batters to have aggregated 1,000-plus runs for CSK, only Dube boasts a 140-plus strike-rate, and his average is bettered only by Michael Hussey (42.09), Ruturaj Gaikwad (41.26) and MS Dhoni (40.69)

Century partnerships for 4th wicket or below for CSK 109* - MS Dhoni & S Badrinath vs KKR, Kolkata, 2010 108* - MS Dhoni & David Hussey vs SRH, Ranchi, 2014 104 - Ruturaj Gaikwad & Shivam Dube vs LSG, Chennai, 2024 102* - Ambati Rayudu & Ravindra Jadeja vs MI, Delhi, 2021 101 - MS Dhoni & Ambati Rayudu vs RCB, Bengaluru, 2018

Highest individual scores for CSK (IPL) 127 - Murali Vijay vs RR, Chennai, 2010 117* - Shane Watson vs SRH, Mumbai WS, 2018 final 116* - Michael Hussey vs PBKS, Mohali, 2008 113 - Murali Vijay vs DC, Chennai, 2012 Q2 108* - Ruturaj Gaikwad vs LSG, Chennai, 2024
Most 200-plus totals in Men’s T20 cricket 34 - Somerset 34 - CSK 32 - India 29 - RCB 29 - Yorkshire This was CSK’s 31st 200-plus total in the IPL, five clear of the next best (26 by RCB).
Welcome back. CSK have their impact player - Shardul in and Rahane out.
